--- !u!114 &1004194158
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1004194153}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: ce2c44bc2cdd1f348a3c6e730a764a96, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  newspapers:
  - newspaper: {fileID: 2130458222}
    dialogueText: ' "Your Lolo believes that. He saw the medals himself."

'
    innerMonologueText: 
    believeText: I guess so.
    questionText: Something about this doesn't add up.
    lessonTitle: Fabricated War Record
    lessonDescription: "American military historians and the U.S. National Archives
      found no evidence the 'Ang\u014D' guerrilla unit ever existed. Marcos's medals
      were revoked by a U.S. military review board in 1986. A man can own medals
      he didn't earn."
    dialogueSound: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 412688d750627df4fa70986eab8e3626, type: 3}
    innerMonologueSound: {fileID: 0}
    believeSound: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 6485ce3fbae12e24b96be087de05e55b, type: 3}
    questionSound: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 9f62b36b86e06b24da159ee9061855cc, type: 3}
  - newspaper: {fileID: 1756386562}
    dialogueText: 
    innerMonologueText: ...  Convicted. Then not convicted. Who changed their minds?
    believeText: He was innocent. The court decided.
    questionText: Courts can be pressured. Who were the judges?
    lessonTitle: Justice and Connections
    lessonDescription: "The Supreme Court justices who overturned the conviction
      had ties to the Marcos family's political circle. Passing the bar exam is real
      \u2014 Marcos was genuinely intelligent. But intelligence and innocence are
      not the same thing."
    dialogueSound: {fileID: 0}
    innerMonologueSound: {fileID: 8300000, guid: e54eb5c21fe63aa4782e185bcd613e1c, type: 3}
    believeSound: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 3c6d10b582ab9df44ad540f8e74aa24e, type: 3}
    questionSound: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 04821f9ce0eacd24aa5256c2e34fef8d, type: 3}
  - newspaper: {fileID: 1474734789}
    dialogueText: ' "Your Lolo voted for him. He said: finally, someone who looks
      like he means it."

'
    innerMonologueText: 
    believeText: ' A landslide means the people chose him. That counts.'
    questionText: What did he promise? And to whom?
    lessonTitle: 'HISTORY: The Image Before the Power'
    lessonDescription: 'Marcos ran on a carefully built image: war hero, brilliant
      lawyer, self-made strongman. His 1965 campaign was one of the most expensive
      in Philippine history to that point. Image and money together can produce a
      landslide. A landslide is not the same as a mandate.'
    dialogueSound: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 488cc918e920f864c8aa3c25d7921b03, type: 3}
    innerMonologueSound: {fileID: 0}
    believeSound: {fileID: 8300000, guid: b132f14cac1f49c45b917adc4e09c893, type: 3}
    questionSound: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 62b70c07ea81ae647a074ccc5b575253, type: 3}
  - newspaper: {fileID: 827242588}
    dialogueText: ' "The road in front of this house was paved three weeks before
      the election. First time in twenty years. Then the trucks were gone."

'
    innerMonologueText: ... Paved before the vote. Gone after. What does that make
      the road?
    believeText: He still won. People voted for him.
    questionText: Can you call it a real election if the government funds one side?
    lessonTitle: 'HISTORY: Spending the Country to Win'
    lessonDescription: "Operation Sagittarius \u2014 Marcos's internal name for his
      re-election campaign \u2014 drained the national treasury. The peso devalued.
      Inflation spiked. The students who took to the streets in 1970 were protesting,
      in part, because Marcos had spent the country's money to keep himself in power.
      The re-election was legal. What it cost was not.     "
    dialogueSound: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 462995079d358b14eb1bfa76fb64a934, type: 3}
    innerMonologueSound: {fileID: 0}
    believeSound: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 98aedfe7e7affc447bfbf200ae06fc24, type: 3}
    questionSound: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 8db05e44ea4a4f84a82db58bda0a99dd, type: 3}
  - newspaper: {fileID: 773760861}
    dialogueText: '"Your tita was at one of those rallies. She didn''t tell your
      grandfather. He found out anyway."

'
    innerMonologueText: ' She marched and didn''t tell anyone. I wonder if she was
      scared.

'
    believeText: There was real unrest. He had to restore order.
    questionText: "Calling protesters enemies \u2014 is that how you answer questions?\r\n"
    lessonTitle: 'The Streets Before the Silence '
    lessonDescription: 'The First Quarter Storm was the last period of open mass
      protest before Martial Law. Students were raising legitimate grievances about
      poverty, corruption, and political dynasties. Marcos framed all of it as communist
      subversion. That framing would become the official justification for what came
      next. '
    dialogueSound: {fileID: 8300000, guid: e087ee11f8ff6f743af3f6bb6f887f37, type: 3}
    innerMonologueSound: {fileID: 0}
    believeSound: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 034c83ea974960e48951eea9f049cbdc, type: 3}
    questionSound: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 091b2b9f7ee679744a499b2f33b84a3e, type: 3}
  - newspaper: {fileID: 1156378585}
    dialogueText: ' "That''s my sister''s. I thought I lost that.Ricky was her son. 
      He was nineteen."'
    innerMonologueText: ...  This is the first time she's told me this.
    believeText: ' I believe her.'
    questionText: ' What happened to Ricky?'
    lessonTitle: ' The Weight of Testimony'
    lessonDescription: "Fear does not begin the night the announcement is made. It
      builds in small decisions \u2014 what not to say, who not to call, which letters
      to burn. The Bantayog ng mga Bayani archives contain thousands of personal
      documents like this one, submitted by families decades later. They are among
      the most honest records of what the period felt like from the inside."
    dialogueSound: {fileID: 8300000, guid: b7a8e930a1891bb42842088ad96075cd, type: 3}
    innerMonologueSound: {fileID: 0}
    believeSound: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 87c33d60f0efda347887a604fa34548d, type: 3}
    questionSound: {fileID: 8300000, guid: d4a2577c0fd1b664fa8e9541e1ed80e9, type: 3}
  - newspaper: {fileID: 641651971}
    dialogueText: '"I remember where I was when I heard. I thought: this is it. Something
      is starting."

'
    innerMonologueText: '... A bombing. And within days, he had already decided who
      did it.

      ... And he used it to take away a right. Just like that.

'
    believeText: Communists were a real threat. He had to act fast.
    questionText: ' How do you suspend a legal right in days? Who benefits most from
      this bombing?'
    lessonTitle: The Rehearsal
    lessonDescription: 'The Plaza Miranda bombing was never conclusively solved.
      Marcos blamed the CPP; later evidence pointed elsewhere. What matters historically
      is what Marcos did with it: he suspended habeas corpus for the first time,
      tested public reaction, and established the legal framework he would use in
      full thirteen months later when he declared Martial Law. Plaza Miranda was
      the rehearsal. September 21, 1972 was the performance. '
    dialogueSound: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 016e6ae2e83d3de4da1ac5d1f78789e9, type: 3}
    innerMonologueSound: {fileID: 0}
    believeSound: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 58f594f8d4781d44fb0bacea1e80abcf, type: 3}
    questionSound: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 6a77894b0d7a0d74fa245f5e9a03f434, type: 3}
  - newspaper: {fileID: 1651901888}
    dialogueText: '"They all say that. In the end, they all say exactly that."

'
    innerMonologueText: "...  After everything in this folder \u2014 the medals,
      the courts, the numbers, the testimonies, the shoes \u2014 I have to decide
      what I believe."
    believeText: Some of it. Not all of it.
    questionText: Almost none of it. Not without proof.
    lessonTitle: 
    lessonDescription: 
    dialogueSound: {fileID: 8300000, guid: c8ac0b7d1deb08049ad069d5b5e20781, type: 3}
    innerMonologueSound: {fileID: 0}
    believeSound: {fileID: 8300000, guid: 93872451e7dc45e4496aee6661b5d5d6, type: 3}
    questionSound: {fileID: 8300000, guid: e2aa2a467aba1b741803b6aa541ab059, type: 3}
